  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All blood cultures taken in the NICU during the study period.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Bacteria that are normal flora of the skin such as Coagulase negative staphylococci or
             Streptococci Viridans are considered, except if grown in two sets of cultures or in
             the presence of laboratory and clinical indices of infection.
      </textblock>
